Genome Annotation Library (GAL)

To install a basic functioning GAL you'll need a few Perl modules
installed via CPAN (http://www.cpan.org/).  An installation script has
been provided which will automatically install all the dependencies
for you.  There are some accessory scripts within the GAL package that
require additional dependencies, and the install script will ask you
if you want to install these.  You can answer either yes or know and
it won't affect the basic functionality of the GAL library.  The
instructions below are divided into two sections, 1) a quick and easy
install and 2) full installation instructions.

1) GAL Quick Install:

   ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
   perl Build.PL
   sudo ./Build installdeps
   ./Build test
   ./Build install
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   
2) GAL Complete Installation Instructions:

   a) Linux

      i) Red Hat, Fedora, CentOS and other Linux systems that use a
         yum package manager:

	 Install a set of developer tools (All we really need is the
	 gcc compiler but it doesn't hurt to round out your
	 installation). Type and answer Yes to the prompts:

	 ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
	 sudo yum update # If you linux installation is out of date.
	 sudo yum groupinstall "Development Tools"
	 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	 If you want to install additional graphics libraries required
	 by optional GAL accessory script you need to install the GD
	 library (http://libgd.bitbucket.org/). Type and answer Yes to
	 the prompts:

	 ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
	 sudo yum install gd-devel
	 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	 Red Hat likes to keep it's tools very retro, so here we'll
         update part of our perl installation to make installing and
         testing GAL easier. Type and accept defaults at prompts:

	 ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
	 sudo cpan TAP::Harness
	 sudo cpan Module::Build
	 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

      ii) Debian, Ubuntu and other Linux systems that use the Advance
          Packaging Tool (i.e. apt-get):

	 Install a set of developer tools (All we really need is the gcc compiler
	 but it doesn't hurt to round out your installation).

	 ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
	 sudo apt-get update # If your linux installation is out of date.
	 sudo apt-get install build-essential
	 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	 If you want to install additional graphics libraries
	 required by optional GAL accessory script you need to
         install the GD library (http://libgd.bitbucket.org/). Type

	 ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
	 sudo apt-get install libgd2-xpm-dev
	 ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   b) Mac OSX:

      Install XCode from the App Store.  Point your browser here
      https://developer.apple.com/xcode/ and follow the link to the
      App Store.

      If you want to install additional graphics libraries required by
      optional GAL accessory script you need to install the GD
      library (http://libgd.bitbucket.org/).  We won't offer detailed
      instructions here - Google ("install libgd mac osx") is your
      friend.      

   For all systems we now install GAL.

   ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
   tar -xzvf GAL.tar.gz
   cd GAL
   perl Build.PL
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   When installing a minimal base installation of GAL answer 'N'
   when asked if you want to install the optional recommended
   modules otherwise answer yes, but make sure you've install GD as
   described above.

   ---------------------------------------- COMMAND LINE ----------------------------------------
   sudo ./Build installdeps
   ./Build test
   ./Build install
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

      
Have a look at the examples in GAL/bin and look at the documentation in GAL/docs/html.

Please report any errors to the mailing list.

http://sourceforge.net/p/song/mailman/
